Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.06,0:00:02.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1\pos(621,542)}It's the Duel Carnival Final!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.94,0:00:05.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1\pos(624,546)}I started my Duel with Tron in the Sphere Field.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.40,0:00:09.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1\pos(670,555)}The both of us have Summoned three Numbers, and the real fight begins now!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.36,0:00:11.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1\pos(656,539)}I won't allow myself to lose!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.94,0:00:13.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm gonna bring it to 'im!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.24,0:00:21.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To think you {\i1}also{\i0} called out three...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.00,0:00:23.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seems you have some luck on your side.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.28,0:00:27.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't luck!\N This is just how skilled I am!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.46,0:00:31.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can win with this battle formation!\N Pass right through him, Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.84,0:00:32.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.76,0:00:35.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate Leviath Dragon's effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.62,0:00:41.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I detach one of its Overlay Units to increase its Attack Power by 500 points!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.68,0:00:44.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Leviath Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.10,0:00:45.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack Shining White Knight Illuminator!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.73,0:00:48.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vice Stream!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.38,0:01:02.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once again! Go on, Aspiring Emperor - Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.43,0:01:04.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack Genome Heriter!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.47,0:01:09.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hope Sword Slash!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.10,0:01:22.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's hardly anything to get too excited about.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.72,0:01:28.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I still have the 3000 Attack Power Acid Golem on my field!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.49,0:01:33.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not done! I activate a Magic from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.60,0:01:36.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Xyz Triangle Force!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.95,0:01:41.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I have three or more Xyz Monsters on my field,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.34,0:01:44.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can destroy one card on my opponent's field!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.28,0:01:50.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go! Destroy Acid Golem!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.13,0:01:59.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you had that card in reserve, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.72,0:02:03.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tron! Now I've defeated all your Numbers!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.09,0:02:07.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm starting to think it'll actually happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.46,0:02:09.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tron doesn't have any set cards or even a hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.73,0:02:13.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he doesn't Summon a Monster on his next turn...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.15,0:02:15.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma's gonna win!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.03,0:02:16.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go for it, Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.70,0:02:24.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I end my turn now!\N So bring it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.95,0:02:30.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm starting to think you {\i1}really{\i0} believe you can defeat me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.27,0:02:34.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I do! For both III and Kaito,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.21,0:02:36.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm definitely gonna beat you!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.22,0:02:39.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have three Numbers on your field.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.01,0:02:43.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems the battlefield is finally ready for me to get serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.01,0:02:45.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.90,0:02:48.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is my Destiny Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.45,0:02:50.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna bring it to 'im!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.97,0:02:52.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.52,0:02:59.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I go now! I activate the effect of the Heraldic Beast Unicorn in my Graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.32,0:03:02.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By Banishing this card from the Graveyard,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.88,0:03:06.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can negate the effect of one Xyz Monster in the Graveyard...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.60,0:03:08.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...in order to Special Summon it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.79,0:03:12.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Show yourself, Shining White Knight Illuminator!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.75,0:03:19.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I activate the effect of the other Heraldic Beast Unicorn in the Graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.08,0:03:23.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll Special Summon the Genome Heriter in my Graveyard the same way!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.56,0:03:28.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use Summoning that Monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.73,0:03:31.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Monsters have the higher Attack Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.71,0:03:37.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, he didn't bring back the Monsters so he could attack with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.57,0:03:38.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.42,0:03:45.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If attacking was his goal, he would have revived the 3000 Attack Power Acid Golem.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.11,0:03:50.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Magic Card, Reborn Medallion, from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.27,0:03:55.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card revives a Level Four or lower Heraldic Beast from my Graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.47,0:04:00.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Revive! Heraldic Beast Bernard's Falcon!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.64,0:04:12.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate Bernard's Falcon's effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.00,0:04:15.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When this card appears on the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.27,0:04:20.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it can change all the Monsters on my field to the same level.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.82,0:04:27.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's changing the levels of his Xyz Monsters?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.16,0:04:31.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now he has three Level Four Monsters on his field!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.55,0:04:32.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.62,0:04:38.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Overlay Illuminator, Genome Heriter, and Bernard's Falcon!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.72,0:04:50.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I build the Overlay Network using these three Monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.47,0:04:52.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Xyz Summon!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.64,0:04:55.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Show yourself, Number 69!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.10,0:05:00.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me to show you my {\i1}real{\i0} trump card!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.11,0:05:07.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God Medallion - Coat of Arms!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.16,0:05:15.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that Number has finally appeared...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.17,0:05:24.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the Number that made quick work of Neo Galaxy-Eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.30,0:05:25.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.35,0:05:35.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the Number that makes up the very essence of Tron's desire for revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.44,0:05:43.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How it hurts.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.03,0:05:46.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hatred pours out from within me and suffocates me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.07,0:05:48.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I no longer need this mask.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.16,0:05:53.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, my Duel with you two will be the last one.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.20,0:05:56.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When it's all over, my memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.37,0:06:00.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...rather, {\i1}anything and everything{\i0}, will be stolen away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.42,0:06:03.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make an {\i1}exception{\i0} and {\i1}show you{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.63,0:06:05.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...my true form!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.84,0:06:12.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That is...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.95,0:06:17.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Byron...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.74,0:06:28.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Advance, advance, beyond the limits of your strength
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.08,0:06:34.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Come along with me and burn our flame of life
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.98,0:06:50.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hey, my friends, what scenery do you suppose
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.11,0:06:56.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}awaits us on the other side of this hill?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.57,0:07:01.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hey, my friends, let's climb it together
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.74,0:07:07.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's too soon for us to turn back now
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.00,0:07:12.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The time has come to combine\N together the power dwelling inside me
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.25,0:07:18.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Gotta release my Soul Drive
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.84,0:07:23.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Advance, advance, beyond the limits of your strength
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.06,0:07:28.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Come along with me and burn our flame of life
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.44,0:07:34.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Keep running, keep running, until you get there
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.69,0:07:40.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Once again, once again, keep those challenges coming
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.11,0:07:46.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My friends, keep on living in the here and now
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.49,0:07:52.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Keep pressing onward together no matter what happens
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.55,0:08:15.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-His face...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.72,0:08:23.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(456,485)}"Number 66: The Terrifying Duel!\N Arise, Hero of Bond ZEXAL!"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.68,0:08:20.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes... While I wandered the threshold between the Parallel Worlds,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.56,0:08:23.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I ended up with the form you see before you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.25,0:08:30.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(635,522)}A heart of revenge is the only thing\N that remains in this body of mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.19,0:08:36.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tron... Does this mean your true form is a being not of this human planet?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.54,0:08:44.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That AR is so freakin' cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.08,0:08:45.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe he even changed his appearance!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.83,0:08:47.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the Final for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.50,0:08:50.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're wrong! That's no AR!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.30,0:08:53.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To summarize, that's his true form!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.34,0:08:55.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, run away...!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.13,0:08:57.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guys, keep it together!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.29,0:09:01.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's going to root for Yuma if we don't?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.83,0:09:04.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.13,0:09:09.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma! Astral! Have a look at my power!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.05,0:09:13.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the ultimate Number I've gotten my hands on!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.67,0:09:16.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And this guy has a very {\i1}special {\i0}effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.82,0:09:21.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Coat of Arms can't be destroyed by Card Effects,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.63,0:09:25.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and he negates the effects of {\i1}all{\i0} Monsters on the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.83,0:09:29.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He can then make their effects his own!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.08,0:09:32.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He can make the effects of other Monsters his own?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.42,0:09:35.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. No matter what Monster it may be,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.63,0:09:38.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they are completely helpless before Coat of Arms!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.33,0:09:43.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you that friendship and hope mean {\i1}nothing{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.30,0:09:46.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Coat of Arms' effect activates!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.05,0:09:48.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God Medallion Hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.99,0:10:11.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Their Monster Effects were stolen!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.00,0:10:14.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I guess I'll use them right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.96,0:10:18.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate Coat of Arm's effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.02,0:10:22.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By detaching one Overlay Unit, I can use the stolen Leviath Dragon's effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.96,0:10:27.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning Coat of Arm's Attack Power goes up 500 points!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.39,0:10:32.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I activate the effect of the Heraldic Beast Leo from my Graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.28,0:10:35.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When one of my Monster's Attack Power changes,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.34,0:10:39.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can Banish this card and take the same amount of added Attack Power
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.01,0:10:42.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and decrease the Attack Power of one of my opponent's Monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.96,0:10:44.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leviath Dragon's Attack Power was...!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.33,0:10:50.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, go do it! Bury Leviath Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.45,0:10:53.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take this! God Rage!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.79,0:11:14.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The power of his Number is incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.62,0:11:16.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very interesting, Byron.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.61,0:11:20.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To think you would go this far to realize your desire for revenge!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.00,0:11:21.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.13,0:11:24.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Are you all right, Yuma?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.80,0:11:26.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I'm hanging in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.00,0:11:27.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hanging in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.95,0:11:31.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's about time you give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.91,0:11:37.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike the useless III, IV, and V, I'm invincible.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.51,0:11:43.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. You can say this Coat of Arms represents the difference in strength between parent and child!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.01,0:11:45.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Between parent and child, huh?\
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.14,0:11:48.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It {\i1}is{\i0} true that Monster is {\i1}exactly{\i0} like you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.83,0:11:50.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.81,0:11:52.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand completely now!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.66,0:11:56.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For III, IV, and even V...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.33,0:12:00.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were great people! They were splendid!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.22,0:12:02.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They frantically supported you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.82,0:12:07.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To the very end, all of them were worried about you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.34,0:12:09.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet, why do such nice guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.83,0:12:14.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...have to throw everything away for someone like you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.92,0:12:19.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the natural thing for a parent and child to do for each other!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.74,0:12:21.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that isn't right!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.62,0:12:23.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They believed in you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.63,0:12:26.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That you'd return to them some day!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.00,0:12:27.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.39,0:12:32.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why couldn't you be a little nicer to them after returning?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.67,0:12:36.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why'd you start pushing them to a dead end for something as boring as revenge?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.29,0:12:41.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A child like you couldn't possibly understand...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.83,0:12:43.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I {\i1}do{\i0} understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.83,0:12:49.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand how lonely it feels when your father goes missing!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.08,0:12:53.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every one of them have been lonely since you went missing!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.25,0:12:59.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And they still gave it their best despite the tears it brought them!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.88,0:13:02.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up! I won't let you sit here and...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.05,0:13:06.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}III...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.89,0:13:07.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}IV...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.76,0:13:09.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}V...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.31,0:13:12.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Memories... of my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.04,0:13:18.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All of it... All of it, along with my face...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.13,0:13:23.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't give up on this Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.17,0:13:29.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until I deliver to you what they've all entrusted me with,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.74,0:13:31.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't ever give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.98,0:13:36.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine then. I'll let you fall prey to my Coat of Arms instantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.87,0:13:39.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll end my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.40,0:13:41.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Astral!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.42,0:13:43.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.49,0:13:48.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ZEXAL. If we want to beat him, we have no choice but to use ZEXAL.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.64,0:13:55.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, this Sphere Field is a psuedo-space created to mimic the Parallel Worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.62,0:13:57.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same as the Empreror's Key.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.02,0:14:00.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can use ZEXAL here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.29,0:14:03.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, there are countless people watching this Duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.68,0:14:05.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter what they think!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.63,0:14:08.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as it lets me deliver their feelings to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.65,0:14:11.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do it, Astral!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.67,0:14:15.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come along with me, Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.82,0:14:18.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna bring it to 'em!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.83,0:14:19.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.54,0:14:21.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...along with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.38,0:14:23.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Overlay!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.10,0:14:47.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the moment two distant souls cross over, the legendary power will come forth!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.68,0:14:55.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Xyz Change!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.91,0:14:57.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ZEXAL!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.38,0:15:07.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Did he say ZEXAL...?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.72,0:15:12.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- What the heck is that?\N - He transformed!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.36,0:15:20.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the power of Yuma and Astral's bond!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.79,0:15:24.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Why's he doing it when everyone's watching?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.54,0:15:26.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To summarize, I wonder myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.90,0:15:28.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C-Cat...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.31,0:15:30.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe they all think it's just AR.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.71,0:15:34.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, Yuma looks really cool right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.55,0:15:36.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He looks like a real hero, doesn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.41,0:15:37.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.08,0:15:39.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's so cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.03,0:15:43.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! That's a genuine hero!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.08,0:15:47.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Tokunosuke, stop that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.87,0:15:52.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's ZEXAL! It's our hero who protects Heartland!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.53,0:15:55.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And his name's ZEXAL, or not!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.26,0:15:56.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ZEXALornot?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.30,0:15:57.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ZEXALornot?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.67,0:15:59.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah! So he's called ZEXALornot?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.71,0:16:00.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I like it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.81,0:16:01.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ZEXALornot!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.16,0:16:04.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, no... When I said "or not"...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.81,0:16:13.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ZEXALornot! ZEXAlornot! ZEXALornot!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.89,0:16:20.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-We might... have a huge misunderstanding\N on our hands here... or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.88,0:16:27.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ZEXALornot! ZEXALornot! ZEXALornot!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.34,0:16:29.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well... Guess it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.21,0:16:35.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing... So many people are cheering for Yuma and Astral.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.16,0:16:48.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ZEXALornot! ZEXALornot! ZEXALornot!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.52,0:16:52.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe you were hiding that combination ability of yours this whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.03,0:16:55.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did they say "ZEXALornot"...?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.66,0:16:59.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about the tiny details.\N Just focus on the Duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.06,0:17:01.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right... I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.90,0:17:04.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.96,0:17:08.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma! Let's Chaos Xyz Change!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.71,0:17:14.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right! I use Aspiring Emperor - Hope as Xyz Material in order to Xyz Change!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.87,0:17:19.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Show yourself, Chaos Number 39!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.64,0:17:24.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aspiring Emperor - Hope Ray!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.82,0:17:37.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So Aspiring Emperor - Hope Ray makes an appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.49,0:17:42.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's useless. I activate Coat of Arm's effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.41,0:17:44.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God Medallion Hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.04,0:17:49.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hope Ray, I'll steal all of your Monster Effects!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.77,0:17:52.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let you! I activate a Magic Card!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.50,0:17:53.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seven Store!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.42,0:17:59.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By releasing one of our Xyz Monsters, Seven Store allows us to draw another card!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.64,0:18:02.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I select Terror-byte!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.53,0:18:06.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And when the Monster is released, for the number of Overlay Units it had,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.52,0:18:10.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can draw another card!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.87,0:18:14.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Terror-byte had two Overlay Units attached to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.51,0:18:17.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I can now draw three times!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.71,0:18:20.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything is inevitable in the strongest Duelist's Dueling!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.71,0:18:23.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even the cards they draw can be created by the Duelist!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.83,0:18:26.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Astral!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.05,0:18:28.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All light, give me power!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.39,0:18:31.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gather into my right hand and illuminate a path toward hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.92,0:18:37.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shining Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.10,0:18:41.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ZEXAL Weapon's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.37,0:18:45.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Coat of Arms can negate the effects of its opponent's Monsters and absorb them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.97,0:18:49.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you can't steal the effect of \Nthe ZEXAL Weapon treated as an Equip!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.01,0:18:52.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Very well thought out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.90,0:18:57.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I equip ZEXAL Weapon - Lightning Blade!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.10,0:19:01.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This ZEXAL Weapon does not need to be Summoned on the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.37,0:19:06.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Instead it can be directly equipped to Hope Ray, and it gains 1200 Attack Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.28,0:19:09.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, when this card is equipped,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.70,0:19:13.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic and Trap Cards we control cannot be destroyed!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.04,0:19:24.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Hope Ray!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.18,0:19:28.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Among the effects snatched by Coat of Arms,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.06,0:19:30.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it doesn't have the power to evade this one!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.33,0:19:34.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hope Sword Lightning Blade!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.70,0:19:37.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.72,0:19:41.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it... I've been waiting for this attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.16,0:19:44.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate Coat of Arm's effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.86,0:19:47.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the opponent attacks,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.33,0:19:49.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by detaching one Overlay Unit,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.87,0:19:52.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this card can destroy one card on the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.54,0:19:56.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I select Aspiring Emperor - Hppe Ray and destroy it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.13,0:19:56.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.41,0:19:59.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me to show you...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.66,0:20:03.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...the {\i0}original {\i1}power of the god!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.37,0:20:06.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Coat of Arms!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.85,0:20:09.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God Slaughter!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.53,0:20:19.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the effect of Lightning Blade!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.37,0:20:22.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the Monster equipped with it is destroyed in battle,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.42,0:20:27.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can return ZEXAL Weapon to my hand\N in order to negate its destruction!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.12,0:20:34.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More of your tricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.83,0:20:37.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the battle still continues, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.72,0:20:39.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, your little hope play ends here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.35,0:20:43.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take him down, Coat of Arms!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.04,0:20:46.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Crush Hope Way into nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.93,0:20:49.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,, I activate Rescueleton Pig’s effect from my Graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.81,0:20:51.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From the Graveyard?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.31,0:20:54.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When a Monster on our field would be destroyed,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.02,0:20:56.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by Banishing Rescueleton Pig from the Graveyard,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.72,0:21:01.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it negates the destruction and makes the damage zero!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.18,0:21:23.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You saved me, Rescueleton!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.51,0:21:26.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop fooling around!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.17,0:21:29.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe you had that Monster set up in your Graveyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.42,0:21:33.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I equip Hope Ray once again with ZEXAL Xyz Change- Weapon Change!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.25,0:21:49.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one card face-down and end my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.03,0:21:58.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure are persistent. I expected no less for Kazuma's son.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.16,0:22:01.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the splitting image of that dull man.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.17,0:22:04.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't ever give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.38,0:22:09.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tron! I swear to collect everyone's feelings and send them to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.50,0:22:25.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We stand tall, until we have victory in our grasp
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.89,0:22:31.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Move on ahead, speeding up our throbbing beats
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.90,0:22:41.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Listen boys and girls, here's the secret to boys and girls like you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.36,0:22:46.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You're really just so spontaneous, wild as can be
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.24,0:22:47.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I bet you didn't know?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.78,0:22:50.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You might be a handful, but what's wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.37,0:22:52.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Be up to no good, but learn for real
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.00,0:22:58.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Go the unpredictable route and shuffle your cards with a goal in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.25,0:23:03.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Whenever you feel like you've lost your way, just take a minute to close your eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.51,0:23:09.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Shout "stop!" with all you've got, and there's your boundary line.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.39,0:23:15.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We stand tall, until we have victory in our grasp
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.69,0:23:21.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We won't just stop here, not when we don't want to have any regrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.19,0:23:26.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if we get hurt, we can't just hesitate now
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.49,0:23:31.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We won't just give up, not when our future's a lot brighter than our today
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.87,0:23:37.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Seriousness... It'll only make us keep fighting even harder
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.33,0:23:42.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We'll always get as fascinated as we want, and we'll fight on every day
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.78,0:23:57.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(646,582)}In the Final of the W.D.C., \Nthis prolonged battle is finally about to end!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.12,0:24:01.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(650,581)}And the true goal of the Sphere Field is finally revealed!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.16,0:24:04.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, we can't allow ourselves to lose this battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.92,0:24:06.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ZEXAL Weapon was...!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.34,0:24:09.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything rides on this final draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.26,0:24:12.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take our all-new attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.43,0:24:14.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on Yu-Gi-Oh! ZeXal!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.64,0:24:17.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Believe in Victory! The Final Shining Draw!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.56,0:24:19.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.93,0:24:23.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just when we finally reveal our cool-looking form,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.69,0:24:25.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,why'd Tokunosuke have to go name it ZEXALornot?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.10,0:24:28.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Warrior of Love and Justice, ZEXALornot.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.81,0:24:31.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Warrior of Victory and Courage, ZEXALornot.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.76,0:24:34.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you shouldn't like it!
